	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=169064><span id= >docalla</span></a><br><span id=notbold>96 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.17]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Yeah, you can. Earth pet is indeed very useful here for the root (one of the few places it is). I got this item today at 51, was using Vocerate Earth... just summon pet, Shield of Lava, pull mob with Ceramic Band, let pet tank him. Goal is to keep pet alive, his HP doesn't matter... sometimes I needed to toss a Shock of Swords too, sometimes I didn't. After the fight, Reclaim Energy with one of your focus items, summon pet again, repeat. Since you're medding all through the fight, there's literally zero downtime. Just make sure you come with at least 5 or so stacks of malachite.<br><br>I'd recommend you get 51 so you can use Voc: Earth but if you're 50 I guess you can try it with a focused 49 Earth pet. If you find that it's taking too much damage though, I suggest just using Monster Summoning II. No root, but it has pretty much the same HP as Voc: Earth does.<br><br>BTW, my casting skills aren't superb (Evo, Alt, Conj and Abj are high, but Div is only about 90), and this item started out for me at 4 WIS 4 INT 8 HP 8 MANA 8 SVM and no Spell Haste II.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
